---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy Policy for Food Scanner and Glasshole iOS apps from Scaling Human."
  path="/privacy.html"
>
  <article class="container prose">
    <header class="page-header">
      <p class="page-header__kicker">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="page-header__title">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="page-header__lead">
        This policy covers the free Food Scanner and Glasshole iOS apps published
        under the Scaling Human name. Those apps explore tools that extend human
        perception and capability.
      </p>
    </header>

    <p class="updated">Last updated: July 8, 2026</p>

    <h2>Summary</h2>
    <p>
      We do not sell personal data. We do not use advertising trackers. The apps
      do not require an account.
    </p>
    <p>
      Food Scanner’s default Local iPhone Vision mode runs on device. Glasshole
      supports Apple Intelligence on compatible devices and runs on device when
      that provider is selected. If you choose a third-party, local-network, or
      custom AI provider, the app sends the content needed for your request to
      that provider using the endpoint and API key you configure.
    </p>

    <h2>Food Scanner</h2>
    <p>
      Food Scanner analyzes food images and generates estimated nutrition
      overlays. Scan history is stored locally on your device. If you choose
      Save to Photos, the app saves the generated result image to your photo
      library.
    </p>
    <p>
      When Local iPhone Vision is selected, food images are classified on device
      and quick nutrition estimates are generated on device from those labels.
      When a third-party, local-network, or custom provider is selected, food
      images are sent to that provider for analysis.
    </p>
    <p>
      Nutrition values are AI estimates for general information only and are not
      medical advice.
    </p>

    <h2>Glasshole</h2>
    <p>
      Glasshole records audio only when you start a session. On-device speech
      recognition converts that audio into text for summarization and
      fact-checking. Audio recordings are not saved. Session history is stored
      locally on your device.
    </p>
    <p>
      Use the app only with the consent of everyone being recorded and in
      compliance with local laws and regulations where you use it.
    </p>
    <p>
      When Apple Intelligence is selected on a compatible device, processing runs
      on device. When a third-party, local-network, or custom provider is
      selected, transcripts are sent to that provider for summarization and
      fact-checking.
    </p>
    <p>
      AI fact-check results can be wrong and should not be treated as
      authoritative.
    </p>

    <h2>Optional Companion Apps</h2>
    <p>
      Optional companion apps are distributed from GitHub. They connect to the
      iOS apps over your local Wi-Fi or iPhone Personal Hotspot. The Food Scanner
      companion can send food images to the iOS app. The Glasshole companion
      sends activation and stop gestures and displays results from the iOS app.
    </p>

    <h2>API Keys</h2>
    <p>
      If you configure a third-party AI provider, API keys are stored in the iOS
      Keychain on your device.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>For privacy questions or support, contact:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Email:
        <a href="mailto:srikantha.ballani@gmail.com"
          >srikantha.ballani@gmail.com</a
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        GitHub:
        <a
          href="https://github.com/scalinghuman/experiments"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >https://github.com/scalinghuman/experiments</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>

    <div class="links-row">
      <a href="/support.html">Support</a>
      <a href="/">Home</a>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
